**Item #:** SCP-902

**Object Class:** Keter

**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-902 is permanently stored in Vault Psi-13, located under Buenos Aires. Only personnel already familiar with SCP-902's effect will be chosen to guard the vault. Personnel performing maintenance on the exterior of the vault will be given the cover story that the facility is there to monitor the seismic effects of [[[SCP-1411]]], and will under no circumstances be permitted inside the vault.

At least ten individuals will be on duty at any time in order to prevent any threats to SCP-902 until it is time to destroy it.

Knowledge of SCP-902's properties is classified as a Class-VII security hazard and held under informational exclusion protocols: no personnel with any authority to alter SCP-902's containment procedure may be exposed to this information, and the number of individuals who are cleared for this information must be limited to the smallest number possible.

As such, the only individual with Level-3 or higher clearance who can access this document is O5-10. They must be barred from entry to Vault Psi-13 and are categorically denied write access to this file. A contingent of MTF-Alpha-1 ("Red Right Hand") has been provided with a limited version of these containment procedures, and instructed to intervene if O5-10 takes any action towards the destruction of SCP-902 or alteration of these containment procedures. No other O5 members may have any knowledge of SCP-902.

In the event of a security breach, all Foundation resources will be employed to either re-secure Vault Psi-13, or, failing that, initiate annihilation of the vault and its environs.
 
SCP-902 must be guarded at all times against premature destruction.

**Description:** 
[[collapsible show="+ WARNING: ACCESS TO THIS FILE IS RESTRICTED TO STAFF WITH SECURITY LEVEL 2 OR LOWER" hide="- If you do not hear anything, it is not too late. You have been warned."]]

