[[module ListPages category="fragment" tags="fragment" parent="." order="@URL|random" limit="1"]]
%%content%%
[[/module]]

SCP-902 is a destructive object, entity or future cognitohazard held inside a box labeled SCP-902-A. SCP-902 has never been directly observed, but knowledge of its existence is evident to any individual made aware of SCP-902-A.

SCP-902-A is a wooden box with a sliding lid measuring 12 cm by 18 cm, and 9 cm deep; a human heart would fit neatly inside. It appears empty, despite the presence of SCP-902. When SCP-902-A is closed, an audible heartbeat manifests. This sound can be recorded through analog means only. Individuals exposed to the recording are afflicted with an awareness of SCP-902. It is excruciating.

Once exposed, individuals continually hear the heartbeat on the edge of their hearing, even when not in the presence of SCP-902. There is a perceptible slowing of his heartbeat over time, though it is not reflected in recordings, which show a steady 60 beats per minute. Why the recordings are incorrect is not yet understood. Some personnel also report smelling copper and licorice.

Those told of SCP-902 will become aware of the great danger posed by SCP-902, and know that it has got to be destroyed as soon as the heartbeat stops, but not before.

A rusted iron dagger has been made available. It is decorated with engraved symbols of spirals, now too aged to see clearly, and has a faint scent of mold. There is a vermilion tassel attached to its handle. It measures 15 cm long and 5 cm across. When the time comes, the dagger is to be used to neutralize the anomaly. Other uses are disallowed (though inspection is permitted). Individuals exposed to SCP-902 find the texture comforting. The rust makes it more real. More certain of its task.

Individuals exposed to SCP-902 typically attempt to open and close the box, trying to find the object inside. This is normal behavior. This is all perfectly normal.

SCP-902 must be protected. It has to be secure. Kept safe. Safe from destruction. We need to destroy it. It has to be destroyed. The beating won't stop. It isn't stopping. It isn't. It must be protected.

There is no heart. There is a heart. It has to be destroyed, when the heartbeat stops. We are doing great work. We have to be stopped.

[[include :scp-wiki:component:listusers-1 users="."]]
Don't stab it, %%title%%. It wants you to. It needs you to. Please, %%title%%, find it, stab it. Before it's too late. You can hear it too, can't you?
